The paper focuses on a method for disentangling generative factors in data using a variational autoencoder. This is a topic that is relevant to several sub-categories within computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and computational linguistics (cs.CL). However, given the emphasis on image datasets and classification tasks, cs.LG and cs.CV are the most likely sub-categories.
